Package datamodel

Interface Model<T>

Type Parameters:
T - A generic type
All Known Subinterfaces:
Category<T>, Classification<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
ModelCategory, ModelClassfication
public interface Model<T>
An interface that exposes the services for a model that saves labels of a generic type
Since:
2020-05-03
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
Marcelo Jacinto, David Souto, Gonçalo Tomás
See Also:
ModelClassfication, Classification, Category, ModelCategory, TreeAugmentedNayveBayes

      boolean addLabelIfNotExistent​(T data)
      A method that when implemented should save a label in the Model if it does not exist there yet. Should return true if the label was added and return false if not
      Parameters:
      data - A generic type with a label to be saved
      Returns:
      A boolean that is true if the label was saved
